Kaizer Chiefs celebrates during the Carling Black Label Champion Cup match between Orlando Pirates and Kaizer Chiefs at FNB Stadium on July 29, 2017 in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Soweto giants Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates will renew their rivalry during Saturday's highly anticipated Carling Black Label Cup. The pre-season curtain-raiser promises fireworks with both teams looking to lay a benchmark ahead of the 2018/19 Absa Premiership season. eNCA.com takes a look at the history around the groundbreaking game.